Privacy Policy

Last updated: April 8, 2026

Hum with Hummingbird ("the App") is designed to help you practice humming as a calming breathing exercise. Your privacy is important to us.

What we collect

Nothing. The App does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.

Microphone access

The App uses your iPhone's microphone to detect humming in real time. Audio is processed entirely on your device using on-device signal processing. Audio is never recorded, stored, uploaded, or transmitted to any server.

Data storage

Your humming session history (duration, timestamps, and frequency data) is stored locally on your device using Apple's SwiftData framework. This data never leaves your device unless you choose to export it manually.

Analytics and tracking

The App does not use any analytics services, tracking pixels, advertising SDKs, or third-party data collection tools.

In-app purchases

If you choose to leave a tip through the App, the transaction is handled entirely by Apple through the App Store. We do not receive or store any payment information.

Third-party services

The App does not integrate with any third-party services. There are no external APIs, no cloud storage, and no server-side components.

Children's privacy

The App does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under 13.

Changes to this policy

If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted at this URL with a new "Last updated" date.

Contact

If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact us at hello@joebalich.com.
